		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD><BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD>Chapter 21 &gt;&gt;&gt;<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />Over the next few weeks, Numb Chuck and company train us in how to use a large variety of weapons. An hour of theory, then an hour of live training, and finally an hour of combat, where we do "games" in the giant combat arena. <BR /><BR />We use fake weapons, that only can connect with other weapons and the body armor we wear. This is to prevent injury, and, they keep track of our running score. We do two weapons a day, one in the morning, then a lunch break, then another in the afternoon.<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />We've finished training with all the weapons, and Numb Chuck starts to give a short speach. <BR /><BR />"Well, you've all been trained in all the weapons we have avaible to us. You must choose which weapons to become better at using," Numb Chuck says. "Now, the true battles are about to begin."<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />And at the other end of the Universe, a dark figure, shrouded in shadow, says, "Yes, Numb Chuck. The true battles are just beginning." Then, it laughes, and disappears. All is silent as the grave once more.<BR /><BR /><BR /><BR />End of Book One </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />I just realized that you're doing a series of short stories <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />And I really wish I still had my flareguns <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR /><BR />I like your final sentence, too- "All is as silent as the grave once more."<BR /><BR />Can't wait for it to keep going!<BR /><BR />--Hurricane, Xtreme Daredevil<BR /> </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />Well, they're all connected. In fact, it's almost like one continuous novel! The only reason I have devided it into books is because I wanted to get into third person. It really is tough for there to be a lot of pure plot when writing in first person! <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /><BR />And, I'm sorry about the low quality of the last few chapters. I had already writen, in my mind, the first chapter of the next book. And, it is going to be... well, I'll just leave it at epic. <img class="emoticon emoticon-joking" id="joking" src="https://lego.i.lithium.com/lego/i/emoticons/joking.png" alt="Joking" title="Joking" /> So, I was really excited to start to write the next part of it, without the limitations first person keeps you to.<BR /><BR />-Formic<BR />-Milligan in game
                
            
			
				
			
			
